{"parentUuid":"ce1fe435-c7ea-4f0d-b7ed-897f3884ce67","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/skogix/.local/share/containers","sessionId":"b9e8251b-c2cb-4ad4-b79e-9eb7c996b007","version":"2.1.62","gitBranch":"HEAD","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Au9z9fLRHE6XHx9p9Lkf1A","type":"tool_result","content":"# SearXNG Docker Installation Guide\n\n## Prerequisites\nYou need either Docker or Podman installed. For Docker, add your user to the docker group:\n```bash\nsudo usermod -aG docker $USER\n```\n\n## Pulling Images\n\nThe official images are available at DockerHub and GitHub Container Registry. Pull the latest version:\n\n```bash\ndocker pull docker.io/searxng/searxng:latest\n```\n\nOr lock to a specific version (e.g., 2025.8.1-3d96414):\n```bash\ndocker pull docker.io/searxng/searxng:2025.8.1-3d96414\n```\n\n**Note:** DockerHub rate limits unauthenticated pulls; use the GHCR mirror instead if needed: `ghcr.io/searxng/searxng`\n\n## Basic Container Setup\n\nCreate directories and run the container:\n\n```bash\nmkdir -p ./searxng/config/ ./searxng/data/\ncd ./searxng/\n\ndocker run --name searxng -d \\\n    -p 8888:8080 \\\n    -v \"./config/:/etc/searxng/\" \\\n    -v \"./data/:/var/cache/searxng/\" \\\n    docker.io/searxng/searxng:latest\n```\n\nAccess SearXNG at `http://localhost:8888`\n\n## Volume Mounts\n\nTwo persistent volumes should be mounted:\n- `/etc/searxng` — Configuration files (settings.yml)\n- `/var/cache/searxng` — Data files (faviconcache.db)\n\n## Environment Variables\n\n- `$SEARXNG_*` — Controls SearXNG configuration in server and general settings\n- `$GRANIAN_*` — Configures Granian server options\n- `$FORCE_OWNERSHIP` — Ensures proper file ownership (default: true)\n\n## Management Commands\n\nList containers:\n```bash\ndocker container list\n```\n\nAccess shell for troubleshooting:\n```bash\ndocker container exec -it --user root searxng /bin/sh -l\n```\n\nStop and remove:\n```bash\ndocker container stop searxng\ndocker container rm searxng\n```\n\n## Custom Certificates\n\nMount `/usr/local/share/ca-certificates/` to add certificates, then run `update-ca-certificates` in the container.\n\n## Building Custom Images\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/searxng/searxng.git\ncd ./searxng/\nmake container\n```\n\n**Note:** The documentation recommends using the preconfigured Docker Compose setup for most deployments rather than manual instancing."}]},"uuid":"ea8baea3-0a53-4b76-ac1d-857cd617f9fe","timestamp":"2026-02-28T14:56:52.818Z","toolUseResult":{"bytes":21507,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# SearXNG Docker Installation Guide\n\n## Prerequisites\nYou need either Docker or Podman installed. For Docker, add your user to the docker group:\n```bash\nsudo usermod -aG docker $USER\n```\n\n## Pulling Images\n\nThe official images are available at DockerHub and GitHub Container Registry. Pull the latest version:\n\n```bash\ndocker pull docker.io/searxng/searxng:latest\n```\n\nOr lock to a specific version (e.g., 2025.8.1-3d96414):\n```bash\ndocker pull docker.io/searxng/searxng:2025.8.1-3d96414\n```\n\n**Note:** DockerHub rate limits unauthenticated pulls; use the GHCR mirror instead if needed: `ghcr.io/searxng/searxng`\n\n## Basic Container Setup\n\nCreate directories and run the container:\n\n```bash\nmkdir -p ./searxng/config/ ./searxng/data/\ncd ./searxng/\n\ndocker run --name searxng -d \\\n    -p 8888:8080 \\\n    -v \"./config/:/etc/searxng/\" \\\n    -v \"./data/:/var/cache/searxng/\" \\\n    docker.io/searxng/searxng:latest\n```\n\nAccess SearXNG at `http://localhost:8888`\n\n## Volume Mounts\n\nTwo persistent volumes should be mounted:\n- `/etc/searxng` — Configuration files (settings.yml)\n- `/var/cache/searxng` — Data files (faviconcache.db)\n\n## Environment Variables\n\n- `$SEARXNG_*` — Controls SearXNG configuration in server and general settings\n- `$GRANIAN_*` — Configures Granian server options\n- `$FORCE_OWNERSHIP` — Ensures proper file ownership (default: true)\n\n## Management Commands\n\nList containers:\n```bash\ndocker container list\n```\n\nAccess shell for troubleshooting:\n```bash\ndocker container exec -it --user root searxng /bin/sh -l\n```\n\nStop and remove:\n```bash\ndocker container stop searxng\ndocker container rm searxng\n```\n\n## Custom Certificates\n\nMount `/usr/local/share/ca-certificates/` to add certificates, then run `update-ca-certificates` in the container.\n\n## Building Custom Images\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/searxng/searxng.git\ncd ./searxng/\nmake container\n```\n\n**Note:** The documentation recommends using the preconfigured Docker Compose setup for most deployments rather than manual instancing.","durationMs":6062,"url":"https://docs.searxng.org/admin/installation-docker.html#installation-container"},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"ce1fe435-c7ea-4f0d-b7ed-897f3884ce67"}
