t\nsearxng::logs() {\n  if [[ \"$argc_follow\" == \"1\" ]]; then\n    podman logs -f searxng\n  else\n    podman logs searxng\n  fi\n}\n\n# @cmd Open a shell in the SearXNG container\nsearxng::shell() {\n  podman exec -it --user root searxng /bin/sh -l\n}\n\n# @cmd Start all services\nup() {\n  argc searxng::up\n}\n\n# @cmd Stop all services\ndown() {\n  argc searxng::down\n}\n\n# @cmd List all containers\nlist() {\n  podman ps -a\n}\n\n# See more details at https://github.com/sigoden/argc\neval \"$(argc --argc-eval \"$0\" \"$@\")\"\n","numLines":77,"startLine":1,"totalLines":77}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"0a725c88-1189-4214-9c7f-cecb90409847"}
{"parentUuid":"54b2c45a-eaed-450c-84f5-dbb5747b7336","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/skogix/.local/share/containers","sessionId":"b9e8251b-c2cb-4ad4-b79e-9eb7c996b007","version":"2.1.62","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"rosy-whistling-horizon","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01PTypQfCBwCoeiU6UAiiKGF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see it now. The user modified the Argcfile.sh. They added a `main()` function:\n```bash\n# @cmd SearXNG operations\n# @arg arg podman container arguments\nmain() {\n  echo \"$argc_arg\"\n}\n```\n\nThis is a test/placeholder that echoes the arg. And they set `argc_arg=grafana` when they ran `argc main grafana`, so it output \"grafana\".\n\nBut now I see the bigger picture - the user added `main()` to the Argcfile.sh as a kind of routing function. The description says \"SearXNG operations\" with `# @arg arg` - this seems like they're testing the pattern where `argc main grafana` would dispatch to the grafana script.\n\n\nThe user is showing me the pattern they want: a dispatcher function that routes service names to their corresponding scripts. They said not to touch bash, so they're demonstrating the design approach rather than asking me to implement it directly.\n\nBut now they're shifting gears—they want me to actually run the command and see what happens, then continue building from there. The \"don't touch bash\" constraint was about the earlier design phase, not this implementation phase. So I should understand how the dispatcher works and start implementing the actual service scripts that handle the operations. The user is implementing this themselves and wants me to guide the design. The key pattern is that `argc main <service> [args]` should dispatch to the service script with those arguments passed through. I need to design what the `main()` function should actually do—it should take a service name (with dynamic choices from the scripts directory), accept optional additional arguments, and route them to the corresponding service script.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1280,"cache_read_input_tokens":87651,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1280},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"requestId":"req_011CYancKuxkE5KSt6UYkEXn","type":"assistant","uuid":"ae05eadc-a273-4e00-880d-684623ccbdb9","timestamp":"2026-02-28T16:32:20.238Z"}
{"parentUuid":"ae05eadc-a273-4e00-880d-684623ccbdb9","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/skogix/.local/share/containers","sessionId":"b9e8251b-c2cb-4ad4-b79e-9eb7c996b007","version":"2.1.62","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"rosy-whistling-horizon","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01PTypQfCBwCoeiU6UAiiKGF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The user modified the Argcfile — `main()` is the universal dispatcher. It currently echoes the arg back as a test. Now I can see the full picture:\n\n```\nargc main grafana        → routes to scripts/grafana.sh\nargc main grafana up     → routes to scripts/grafana.sh main up\n```\n\nThe `main()` needs three things designed:\n\n1. **`service` arg** — dynamic choice from `_choice_service` (scans `scripts/*.sh`)\n2. **`action` arg** — `[up|down|logs|shell]`\n3. **`-f/--follow` flag** — passed through to the script\n\nAnd a `_choice_service` function that reads `scripts/` at runtime, so adding a new `.sh` automatically makes it available — no Argcfile changes needed.\n\nThe dispatch call would be:\n```\nargc --argc-run scripts/${argc_service}.sh main ${argc_action} ${argc_follow:+-f}\n```\n\nSo the interface for `main()` in Argcfile.sh:\n\n```bash\n# @cmd Dispatch to a managed service\n# @arg service![`_choice_service`]       Service name\n# @arg action![up|down|logs|shell]       Action to perform\n# @flag -f --follow                      Follow log output (logs only)\n```\n\n```bash\n_choice_service() {\n    ls scripts/*.sh | xargs -n1 basename | sed 's/\\.sh$//'\n}\n```\n\nThat's the full design — one dispatcher, all services discovered dynamically, zero hardcoding. Over to you for the bash."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1280,"cache_read_input_tokens":87651,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1280},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_