{"parentUuid":"cd103c64-bd03-4640-b115-e2890b21efa8","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/skogix/.local/src/container","sessionId":"b9e8251b-c2cb-4ad4-b79e-9eb7c996b007","version":"2.1.62","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"rosy-whistling-horizon","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014LhsZZwcFsvxgxyoPCdnq6","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me provide a comprehensive analysis:\n\n## Comprehensive Analysis\n\n### File Contents Summary\n\nAll requested files have been read:\n- **`/home/skogix/.local/src/container/utils/run-script.sh`** - 124 lines\n- **`/home/skogix/.local/src/container/Argcfile.sh`** - 27 lines\n- **`/home/skogix/.local/src/container/scripts/searxng.sh`** - 10 lines (stub)\n- **`/home/skogix/.local/src/skogterm/utils/run-script.sh`** - 124 lines (identical to container)\n- **`/home/skogix/.local/src/skogterm/scripts/port.sh`** - 22 lines (well-formed example)\n- **`/home/skogix/.local/src/skogterm/scripts/argc-simple.sh`** - 28 lines (argc example)\n\n---\n\n## Answer to Your Questions\n\n### 1. What does run-script.sh do? How does it invoke scripts? What is the JSON data format?\n\n**run-script.sh** is a JSON-to-bash-arguments converter and script runner. It:\n\n1. **Accepts invocation in two ways:**\n   - Direct: `./run-script.sh <script-name> <json-data>`\n   - Symbolic link: `./some-script <json-data>` (derives name from symlink)\n\n2. **JSON data format:** Flat key-value object that gets converted to CLI flags\n   ```json\n   {\n     \"action\": \"up\",\n     \"follow\": true,\n     \"port\": 9000\n   }\n   ```\n\n3. **Conversion logic (lines 70-88):** Uses a sophisticated jq script that:\n   - Converts keys with underscores to dashes: `my_key` → `--my-key`\n   - Handles three value types:\n     - **Arrays:** Repeats flag for each value: `--key val1` `--key val2`\n     - **Booleans:** Only emits flag if true: `--key` (or nothing if false)\n     - **Strings/numbers:** Emits with value: `--key value`\n   - Escapes shell special chars in values (preserves single quotes, newlines, etc.)\n\n4. **Execution chain (line 97):**\n   ```bash\n   eval \"'$script_path' $args\"\n   ```\n   Example: `./scripts/searxng.sh --action up --follow`\n\n5. **Environment setup:**\n   - Loads `.env` file from root\n   - Sets `LLM_ROOT_DIR`, `LLM_script_name`, `LLM_script_CACHE_DIR`\n   - Supports `LLM_OUTPUT` (defaults to tempfile)\n   - Displays results if matched in `LLM_DUMP_RESULTS` regex\n\n---\n\n### 2. How does it relate to the argc @describe/@cmd interface?\n\n**Two completely separate systems:**\n\n**argc system** (in Argcfile.sh):\n- Uses `@cmd`, `@arg`, `@flag` decorators\n- Calls `eval \"$(argc --argc-eval ...)\"` for bash-native argument parsing\n- Dynamically generates completion functions\n- Direct bash invocation: `bash ./scripts/searxng.sh main --action up`\n\n**run-script.sh system** (in utils/):\n- Uses JSON as bridge format\n- For LLM/programmatic invocation\n- Intended as external interface (not direct bash)\n\n**They are NOT integrated.** Argcfile.sh has its own `run()` function that directly execs scripts:\n```bash\nbash ./scripts/${argc_file}.sh main \"${args[@]}\"\n```\nThis bypasses run-script.sh entirely.\n\n---\n\n### 3. What is the full invocation chain: run-script.sh → script → ?\n\n**Chain for run-script.sh approach:**\n```\nExternal caller (Python/Node/LLM)\n    ↓\n./run-script.sh scriptname '{\"action\":\"up\"}'\n    ↓ parse_argv() → script_name=\"scriptname\", script_data='{\"action\":\"up\"}'\n    ↓ setup_env() → export LLM_* vars\n    ↓ jq converter: '{\"action\":\"up\"}' → '--action up'\n    ↓ eval 'scriptpath --action up'\n    ↓\nScript's main() function\n    ↓ Reads $argc_* variables (set by argc --argc-eval)\n    ↓ Outputs to $LLM_OUTPUT\n    ↓\nrun-script.sh checks dump_result() → outputs to stdout\n```\n\n**Chain for Argcfile.sh approach:**\n```\nUser invocation: argc run searxng --action up\n    ↓ Argcfile.sh run() function\n    ↓ Validates script exists and has 'argc --argc-eval'\n    ↓ bash ./scripts/searxng.sh main --action up\n    ↓\nScript's main() and argc integration\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. What makes a script \"compatible\" with run-script.sh?\n\nA script must:\n1. Be executable bash with a `main()` function\n2. Use argc decorators (`@cmd`, `@arg`, `@flag`)\n3. Call `eval \"$(argc --argc-eval \"$0\" \"$@\")\"`\n4. Reference arguments via `$argc_*` variables (set by argc)\n\nExample compatible script structure:\n```bash\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\n\n# @cmd Description\n# @arg action![up|down] Action\n# @flag -f --follow Follow output\n\nmain() {\n  # $argc_action, $argc_follow available here\n  echo \"Action: $argc_action\" >> $LLM_OUTPUT\n}\n\neval \"$(argc --argc-eval \"$0\" \"$@\")\"\n```\n\n**Critical:** The script must NOT be directly invoked with positional args via run-script.sh. It receives everything as flags.\n\n---\n\n### 5. What currently exists in the container repo beyond Argcfile.sh and scripts/?\n\n**Directory structure:**\n```\n/home/skogix/.local/src/container/\n├── .devcontainer/\n│   └── devcontainer.json\n├── .git/               (git repo with commit history)\n├── Argcfile.sh         (argc integration)\n├── Dockerfile\n├── docker-compose.yml\n├── README.md\n├── scripts/            (22 service scripts)\n│   ├── actual.sh\n│   ├── freshrss.sh\n│   ├── gitea.sh\n│   ├── grafana.sh\n│   ├── homepage.sh\n│   ├── immich.sh\n│   ├── jellyfin.sh\n│   ├── mealie.sh\n│   ├── n8n.sh\n│   ├── nextcloud.sh\n│   ├── paperless.sh\n│   ├── pihole.sh\n│   ├── plausible.sh\n│   ├── portainer.sh\n│   ├── prometheus.sh\n│   ├── searxng.sh\n│   ├── syncthing.sh\n│   ├── traefik.sh\n│   ├── uptime-kuma.sh\n│   ├── vaultwarden.sh\n│   └── wireguard.sh\n└── utils/\n    └── run-script.sh\n\nNO /services/ or /lib/ directories exist.\n```\n\n**Docker infrastructure files present:** Dockerfile, docker-compose.yml, devcontainer.json\n**Scripts:** All 22 follow identical stub pattern (TODO implementation, argc decorators, main() + eval)\n\n---\n\n## Key Insights\n\n1. **run-script.sh is a JSON-to-flags adapter** for programmatic/LLM invocation. It's not CLI-friendly.\n2. **Argcfile.sh is the actual CLI interface** using argc framework. It's human-friendly.\n3. **Two systems don't talk to each other.** They're alternative entry points to the same scripts.\n4. **All scripts use argc** for consistent argument parsing, but only Argcfile.sh currently uses run-script.sh is designed for external callers (Python, Node, APIs).\n5. **Bug in run-script.sh line 25:** Uses undefined variable `$tool_name` instead of `$script_name`.\n6. **Container repo structure is minimal:** Just Docker config + 22 service scripts (mostly stubs) + entry points."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a436aaa026fe41208 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 71654\ntool_uses: 17\nduration_ms: 29293</usage>"}]}]},"uuid":"2aa043a7-9263-415b-a9b9-1bd9a3d1171d","timestamp":"2026-02-28T17:47:44.419Z","toolUseResult":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read and understand these files thoroughly:\n\n1. `/home/skogix/.local/src/container/utils/run-script.sh` - the full content\n2. `/home/skogix/.local/src/container/Argcfile.sh` - current state\n3. `/home/skogix/.local/src/container/scripts/searxng.sh` - current state\n4. `/home/skogix/.local/src/skogterm/utils/run-script.sh` if it exists\n5. `/home/skogix/.local/src/skogterm/scripts/port.sh` - example of a well-formed script\n6. `/home/skogix/.local/src/skogterm/scripts/argc-simple.sh`\n\nAlso check: does `/home/skogix/.local/src/container/services/` exist? Does `/home/skogix/.local/src/container/lib/` exist?\n\nI need to understand:\n- What does run-script.sh do? How does it invoke scripts? What is the JSON data format?\n- How does it relate to the argc @describe/@cmd interface?\n- What is the full invocation chain: run-script.sh → script → ?\n- What makes a scri